This mod is entirely standalone and does not touch any vanilla content whatsoever. It should be technically compatible with anything, and broadly compatible with pretty much everything from a game-design pov - use the game rules to disable things if there's a problem.

The Journal Entries do look a little different (and prettier) if you are using the [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=3385002128]Community Modding Framework[/url]

[img]https://i.imgur.com/lQRf9dG.png[/img]
[b]Why?[/b]
[i]This solves two problems that I consider to be critical:
1) The investment pool growing endlessly in the late game without rhyme, reason, or consequence.
2) Countries being able to become tech leaders purely by building universities, no matter how terrible their laws are.[/i]

[b]What does "Populist Legal Innovation" mean?[/b]
[i]This is the era where change largely came about through popular action - so, outcomes that affected these conditions were largely "Populist".
At the end of the day, this is also the era that proved how important the legal framework was for fostering development - so, "Legal".
And, not limited to scientific pursuit, it was innovations in how laws were conceived, written, and enforced, which really created the modern world - so, "Innovations".
Investment and Scientific development were shaped by populist forces that innovated constantly to influence, break, or remake the legal frameworks of the time, and that is what this mod aspires to represent.[/i]

